						               													<description>L&amp;eacute;gion d'honneur is a Miniature Wargame Rule set specifically designed for 28mm&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the work since 2010, these rules allow you to play at the brigade level in 3 to 4 hrs, at the divisional level in 5 to 8 hrs and, for the most dedicated ones, also let you simulate battles between army corps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The principle of these rules is to offer a fair balance between historicity and playability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To achieve that goal a few principles have been adopted:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Play during - what we think - is the most even historical period: 1808 to 1813&amp;#10;     Erase some of the preconceived ideas of wargamers, such as line of fire/sight, English only in defense... to that goal historical researches were done using at least 2 different sources to make it in the rules. &amp;#10;     Stop with the idea that a battle is won by the number of minis removed from the tabletop.&amp;#10;     Take into account formations actually used in that time period.  &amp;#10;     Take into account fatigue and the psychological overwhelming of the troops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It may seem an ambitious project but that is what is on offer, including the fun factor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;LH is easy to get into, offer multiple opportunities to simulate battles, and under certain circumstances allow players to be in complex and challenging situations without being a pain.&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
